This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as argument classification and clustering, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of contextualized word embeddings also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper reports improvements in performance metrics, indicating a possible focus on optimization and algorithmic development, which are common in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval tasks, such as clustering, which suggests a possible fit with the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with argumentation, which is a topic that can be studied in the subfield of cybernetics (cs.CY).
